\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces LLM firewall pipeline architecture. \textit  {How to read this diagram:} Every prompt flows left to right through the Normalizer, then v1 (signature) and v3 (semantic) detectors run in parallel, then a simple OR gate (OR-fusion) decides whether to block or forward to the LLM. Production configuration uses Normalizer + v3 only (57\% TPR, 0\% FAR on clean queries, 0.77\% FAR under obfuscation). Monitoring configuration adds v1 for higher recall (87\% TPR on Phase 1 attacks, 49\% TPR on novel attacks from P6b, 0\% FAR on clean queries, 12.3\% FAR under obfuscation).}}{12}{figure.caption.34}\protected@file@percent }
